title: colour-set-alpha Operator
caption: colour-set-alpha
op-purpose: set the alpha channel of colour values
op-input: a selection of colour values
op-parameter: the new alpha value, from 0 (fully transparent) to 1 (fully opaque)
op-output: the modified colours

<<.from-version "5.5.0">> See ColourPalettes for background.

The <<.op colour-set-alpha>> operator sets the alpha channel of each input colour to the given value, leaving the other components unchanged.

Input values that cannot be parsed as colours are returned as empty strings.

For example, this filter expression makes the current foreground colour half transparent:

```
[function[colour],[foreground]colour-set-alpha[0.5]]
```

See also the following related operators:

* <<.olink colour-set-oklch>> to modify the lightness, chroma or hue of a colour value
